#. type: Title =
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Negative invoices and credit notes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:6
msgid "This BIS supports negative grand totals."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:8
msgid ""
"The argument for negative invoices is to open up for a wider spectrum of "
"invoicing processes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:10
msgid "Examples of such processes are"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:12
msgid ""
"Preliminary (estimated) consumption invoice that is balanced out in a later "
"meter-based invoice;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Pre-payment (with or without CT) is settled through a final invoice; and"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Some user communities prefer to use negative invoice rather than credit note "
"when correcting transactions."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Buyers who value automatic matching of e-invoices to orders or invoicing "
"objects may wish to limit the areas and situations where complex "
"transactions can be accepted and voice their requirements at time of "
"procurement."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:20
msgid "The decision has the following implications on the transaction format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:22
msgid ""
"The invoice (now with “negative invoice capacity”) can function as an "
"alternative to the credit note. Invoice-generating systems may implement "
"either option, while invoice-receiving systems have to support both of them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:23
msgid ""
"The transaction format for credit note has to be designed to accommodate for "
"negative grand total, as well; this is because an entire negative invoice "
"may have to be balanced out by means of a credit note."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: guide/transaction-spec/functionality/negative-invoices.adoc:25
msgid ""
"Attention is drawn to the intrinsic differences between credit note and "
"negative invoice when it comes to convey crediting information."
msgstr ""
